# Git identity and commits (qapitol-evals-kit)

## Author identity (required)

This repo **must** use **local** git config only (not global personal email):

- `user.name` = `Qapitol`
- `user.email` = `*@qapitol.com` (currently `satyam.dixit@qapitol.com`)

Before any `git commit`, run:

```bash
./scripts/verify-git-identity.sh
```

If it fails, fix with:

```bash
git config --local user.name "Qapitol"
git config --local user.email "satyam.dixit@qapitol.com"
```

Do **not** change global `user.email` to personal Gmail for work on this repo.

## No Cursor co-author (required)

- **Never** add `Co-authored-by: Cursor` or `cursoragent@cursor.com` to commit messages.
- **Never** use Cursor/agent trailers that attribute commits to Cursor on GitHub.
- Write commit messages yourself; plain subject + body only.
- If the IDE injects a co-author trailer, amend and remove it before push:

```bash
git commit --amend -m "your message without Co-authored-by lines"
```

## Push checklist

1. `./scripts/verify-git-identity.sh`
2. `git log -1 --format='%an <%ae>%n%B'` — confirm author is Qapitol / @qapitol.com and body has **no** `Co-authored-by: Cursor`
3. Then push
